{"title": "Hand Gagging", "content": "Past Pete: Would somebody tell me what's been goin' on here? Who was that creep, anyways? \n\nSora: Hello? That creep was... [Goofy clamps his hand over Sora's mouth] \n\nGoofy: Sora, that's a secret! Would somebody tell me what's been goin' on here? Who was that creep, anyways?Hello? That creep was... [Goofy clamps his hand over Sora's mouth]Sora, that's a secret!\n\nSimilar to the Finger Muzzle, this is a more direct and easier way of shutting someone up. If Alice is being kidnapped, the best way to prevent her from crying out is by grabbing her and covering her mouth. Not only that, but Bob could easily do it if he just wanted her to stop talking for some reason.\n\nThis gesture can be threatening or playful, depending on the context. Rescuers may sometimes use this if they have to sneak up on a friend from behind and don't want them alerting nearby foes by yelling in surprise. If in hiding, the more self-controlled character may use it to keep the frightened character from crying out inadvertently.\n\nIt bears noting that this method of trying to subdue someone can be defeated if the person doing it is capable of feeling pain, namely by biting down hard on said person's hand.\n\nCompare with Finger Muzzle, \"Shut Up\" Kiss, Standard Female Grab Area, and Finger on Lips. See also Bound and Gagged.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HandGagging?from=Main.PuttingAHandOverHisMouth", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/IMissYou", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/KingdomHeartsII", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Berserk", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Bleach", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Brave10", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/DeathNote", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/DragonBallZ", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/FruitsBasket", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Naruto", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/OnePiece", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/Pokemon", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/SoundEuphonium", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/LoisLane", "/pmwiki/pmwik